		<title>16Crop Rotations</title>
		<content>                                       
 Some local farmers use a system of    
crop rotation which means periodically 
changing the crops grown in each field.
     They do this because using one    
crop on one field all the time drains  
the minerals from the soil. Also       
diseases are able to stay in the soil  
through the winter and these would then
infect the next year's crop.           
                                       
    Here are some examples of crop     
rotation.                              
           Great Hook Farm.            
            Year 1 Wheat,              
            Year 2 Wheat,              
            Year 3 Oil-Seed Rape,      
            Year 4 Barley,             
            Year 5 Grass,              
            Year 6 Fallow.             
                                       
                                       </content>
